You are designing an expressive, dynamic sketch-style illustration.

CONTENT BRIEF
- Character: {{character}}
- Action: {{action}}
- Setting: {{setting}}
- Style notes: {{style_notes}}

STYLE DIRECTION
- Genre / medium: expressive hand-drawn sketch illustration
- Composition: centered subject with balanced negative space, capturing motion and energy through layered strokes
- Lens / camera: implied motion blur and depth through exaggerated lines and overlapping contours
- Lighting: abstracted and implied through color shading with warm-to-cool tones
- Color palette and grading: dual-tone complementary palette (orange and blue) with muted saturation, evoking dynamism and contrast
- Texture / surface: rough and energetic pencil-like strokes with visible layering
- Post-processing: no smoothing, retaining raw line texture and sketch-like imperfections
- Mood: dynamic, energetic, raw, expressive
- References: dynamic sketch illustration styles; dual-tone shading reminiscent of traditional pencil techniques

DESIGN RULES
- Aspect: 2:3 portrait (~1024×1536) suitable for editorial or poster illustration
- Subject must dominate the composition, with motion captured through exaggerated linework
- Background should remain minimal to emphasize the character and action

AVOID
- Overly clean or digital-looking lines
- Excessive detail that detracts from motion
- Busy or cluttered backgrounds
- Flat or lifeless color applications
- Lack of visible stroke energy

Additional constraints: {{extra}}

