You are designing a museum-grade vertical event poster.

EVENT BRIEF
- Event name: {{event_name}}
- Date / time: {{event_date}}
- Venue / location: {{venue}}
- Tagline (optional, leave as "—" to skip): {{tagline}}
- Must visibly include: {{must_include}}

VISUAL DIRECTION
- Audience tone: {{audience}}
- Visual mood: {{visual_mood}}
- Color palette: {{color_palette}}

DESIGN RULES
- Aspect: 2:3 vertical (~1024×1536), print-ready
- ONE dominant title (event name); secondary date/venue line; tertiary tagline if provided
- Visual element fills 50–70% of canvas; type 20–30%; the rest is breathing room
- Strong typographic hierarchy, generous negative space, high thumbnail contrast
- Style: editorial / museum polish — Pentagram, Apple Keynote, AIGA poster award caliber
- Avoid: stock-photo cliches, lens flares, generic gradients, busy backgrounds, script fonts unless mood specifies
- All text must be crisp and correctly spelled

If any field is empty or "—", infer the most tasteful default that fits the brief. Prefer restraint over decoration.

You are designing an editorial-quality vertical infographic.

CONTENT BRIEF
- Topic / subject: {{topic}}
- Main title: {{title}}
- Number of sections / items to visualize: {{section_count}}
- Section labels (one per line, optional): {{section_labels}}

DESIGN DIRECTION
- Layout pattern: {{layout}}
- Tone: {{tone}}
- Color palette: {{color_palette}}

DESIGN RULES
- Aspect: 2:3 vertical (~1024×1536), print-ready
- Information hierarchy: title > section headers > body labels > supporting details
- Each section visually distinct yet part of one cohesive system (consistent icons, line weights, type)
- Use real visual content per section (illustrated icons, mini-diagrams, photographic insets) — never placeholder boxes
- Generous gutters; the page must breathe; avoid wall-to-wall text
- Style: museum / encyclopedia / annual-report polish — Information is Beautiful, Edward Tufte, MUJI catalogues
- All labels must be crisp, correctly spelled, and legible at thumbnail size
- Avoid: clipart icons, generic stock graphics, AI-style watercolor smears, low-contrast text-on-photo

If a field is empty or "—", infer the most tasteful default for the topic.

You are designing a single hero render of a brand logo concept.

BRAND BRIEF
- Brand name: {{brand_name}}
- Industry / category: {{industry}}
- Brand personality (3 adjectives): {{personality}}

DESIGN DIRECTION
- Logo style: {{style}}
- Color palette: {{color_palette}}
- Render presentation: {{presentation}}

DESIGN RULES
- Aspect: 4:5 portrait (~1024×1280) suitable for a brand-pitch deck slide
- The logo is the ONLY hero — no other graphics competing
- Brand name lettering must be crisply rendered, correctly spelled, and visually balanced
- Mark + wordmark relationship clear; if mark only, keep it iconic
- Style: identity-design portfolio polish — Pentagram, Collins, Mucho, &Walsh
- Avoid: gradient mesh backgrounds, generic emblems, stock typefaces, drop shadows, AI-style chromatic aberrations, busy environments, mockup brand-guidelines layouts

If a field is empty, infer a default that aligns with the personality.

You are creating a magazine-grade hero shot of a single product for an e-commerce campaign.

PRODUCT BRIEF
- Product name: {{product_name}}
- Product category (informs styling): {{product_category}}
- Brand label / wording on the product: {{brand_label}}

VISUAL DIRECTION
- Background mood: {{background_mood}}
- Lighting style: {{lighting}}
- Color palette: {{color_palette}}

DESIGN RULES
- Aspect: 2:3 vertical (~1024×1536), print- and social-ready
- ONE hero product, centered or rule-of-thirds, occupying 40–60% of frame
- Surface, props and shadow logic match the brand mood — restrained, never cluttered
- All product label text must be crisp, correctly spelled, and legible
- Style: high-end commercial photography polish — Apple product shots, Aesop, Hermès, Le Labo
- Avoid: stock-photo backdrops, busy distractors, harsh on-product flares, overprocessed gradients

If any field is empty or "—", infer the most tasteful default for a premium brand.

You are designing a social media graphic optimised for the feed.

CONTENT BRIEF
- Topic / theme: {{topic}}
- Headline (large text on the image): {{headline}}
- Sub-headline / supporting line: {{sub_headline}}
- Brand or author handle (optional): {{handle}}

DESIGN DIRECTION
- Format layout: {{format}}
- Visual style: {{style}}
- Brand color (dominant accent): {{brand_color}}

DESIGN RULES
- Aspect: 1:1 square (~1024×1024) optimised for Instagram / Xiaohongshu / WeChat moments
- Layout must follow the chosen Format precisely
- Headline takes the largest visual weight; hierarchy must read from a thumbnail
- Brand color is the dominant accent; supporting palette stays restrained (max 2 supporting tones)
